{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idcf836a8c-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0","identifier":"/us/usc/t48/s1641"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1641"},"text":"§ 1641.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Method of payment of official salaries","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The salaries and travel allowances of the Governor, Lieutenant Governor, the heads of the executive departments, other officers and employees of the government of the Virgin Islands, and the members of the legislature shall be paid by the government of the Virgin Islands at rates prescribed by the laws of the Virgin Islands.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idcf85da8d-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1954-07-22/ch558/s20"},"text":"July 22, 1954, ch. 558, § 20","children":[],"tail":", formerly § 20(c), "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/68/506"},"text":"68 Stat. 506","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/85/851/s6/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 85–851, § 6(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1958-08-28"},"text":"Aug. 28, 1958","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/72/1095"},"text":"72 Stat. 1095","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/90/496/s10"},"text":"Pub. L. 90–496, § 10","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1968-08-23"},"text":"Aug. 23, 1968","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/82/841"},"text":"82 Stat. 841","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idcf85da8e-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idcf85da8f-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"idcf85da90-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Prior to the 1968 amendment of section 20 of act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1954-07-22"},"text":"July 22, 1954","children":[],"tail":", this section constituted subsec. (c) of said section 20. Subsecs. (a) and (b) of said section 20 were classified to sections 1592 and 1598, respectively, of this title. "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/90/496/s10"},"text":"Section 10 of Pub. L. 90–496","children":[],"tail":" consolidated the text of said section 20 into a single unlettered paragraph, classified to this section."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idcf85da91-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1968—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/90/496"},"text":"Pub. L. 90–496","children":[],"tail":" substituted provisions that the salaries and travel allowances of all officials connected with the executive and legislative departments of the government of the Virgin Islands be paid by the government of the Virgin Islands at rates prescribed by the laws of the Virgin Islands for provisions that the salaries of the Governor, the Government Secretary, the government comptroller, and their immediate staffs be paid by the United States, and provisions that the salaries of the heads of the executive departments be paid by the government of the Virgin Islands, such salaries to be paid without the necessity of further appropriations therefor, if the legislature fails to make an appropriation for such salaries."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1958—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/85/851"},"text":"Pub. L. 85–851","children":[],"tail":" provided for the payment of the salary of the government comptroller by the United States instead of by the government of the Virgin Islands."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idcf85da92-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idcf85da93-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1968 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment of provisions of section necessary to authorize the holding of an election for Governor and Lieutenant Governor on ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1970-11-03"},"text":"Nov. 3, 1970","children":[],"tail":", effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1970-01-01"},"text":"Jan. 1, 1970","children":[],"tail":", and all other amendments of provisions of section, unless otherwise expressly provided by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/90/496"},"text":"Pub. L. 90–496","children":[],"tail":", effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1971-01-04"},"text":"Jan. 4, 1971","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/90/496/s16"},"text":"section 16 of Pub. L. 90–496","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t48/s1591"},"text":"section 1591 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idcf85da94-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1958 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/85/851/s6/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 85–851, § 6(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1958-08-28"},"text":"Aug. 28, 1958","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/72/1095"},"text":"72 Stat. 1095","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/85/851/s6/b"},"text":"“This section 6 [amending this section] shall become effective on ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1959-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1959","children":[],"tail":".”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idcf85da95-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Elimination of General Fund Deficits of Guam and Virgin Islands","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/597/tVI/s607"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–597, title VI, § 607","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-12-24"},"text":"Dec. 24, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/3483"},"text":"94 Stat. 3483","children":[],"tail":", as amended by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/357/tVI/s601"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–357, title VI, § 601","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1982-10-19"},"text":"Oct. 19, 1982","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/1712"},"text":"96 Stat. 1712","children":[],"tail":", authorized limited payments to Guam and the Virgin Islands for fiscal years 1982 to 1985 provided the respective governors of those territories submit plans designed to eliminate the respective territories’ general fund deficits by the beginning of fiscal year 1987."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneou